Pop your #kettle{} on to boil. Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown all over, ~{5-6%mins}. While the chicken browns, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}.

Add the shallot, @ground turmeric{2%tsp}, @ground coriander{1%tsp} and half the @cumin seeds{1.5%tsp} to the #pan{}. Cook, stirring, for ~{1-2%mins}, then add the @red split lentils{50%g} and @tomato puree{30%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the @water{300%ml}. Bring to the boil, stir in half the @chicken stock powder{1%tsp}, reduce the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, ~{10%mins}. Meanwhile, toast the remaining @cumin seeds{1.5%tsp} in another large saucepan on medium heat (no oil), ~{1%minute}.

Add the @water for the rice{300%ml}. Bring to the boil then stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and remaining stock powder, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve.

> The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. When the stew has been cooking for 10 mins, stir in the courgette and pop a lid on the pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, for another ~{10-12%mins}.

> If the stew is looking a bit dry, add a splash of water to loosen it up!

Halve the @green chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then finely slice. Pick the @mint{1/2%bunch} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks). In a #small bowl{}, mix the @Greek style natural yoghurt{150%g} with the mint. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Keep to one side.

Your stew is ready when the lentils are soft and the chicken is cooked.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}, then stir in as much green chilli as you fancy (add less if you're not a fan of heat!). Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and serve it in #bowls{} topped with the chicken stew. Add a dollop of minty yoghurt and a sprinkling of any remaining chilli. Enjoy!